events.name: Florida Atlantic Owls at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron threw three touchdown passes, including an early 85-yarder to Kenny Bell, and No. 1 Alabama routed Florida Atlantic 40-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 1 Bama rolls

events.name: LSU Tigers at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: LSU's defense delivered a first-quarter safety and shut out Auburn in the second half to give the second-ranked Tigers a 12-10 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 2 LSU edges Auburn

events.name: Arizona Wildcats at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Redshirt freshman Marcus Mariota threw for 260 yards and two touchdowns, including a 55-yard scoring pass to freshman Bralon Addison late in the third quarter, and No. 3 Oregon beat No. 22 Arizona 49-0 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mariota, No. 3 Oregon rout No. 22 Arizona

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: EJ Manuel threw for a career-high 380 yards and two touchdowns and ran for another 102 yards as fourth-ranked Florida State rallied from a two-touchdown deficit to defeat No. 10 Clemson 49-37 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: FSU rallies in 2nd half, tops Clemson

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray completed his first 12 passes and No. 5 Georgia finally got off to a good start, blowing out Vanderbilt before halftime on the way to a 48-3 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia crushes Vandy

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: John Hubert ran for 130 yards and a touchdown, Jarell Childs scooped up a fumble and returned it for a score and No. 15 Kansas State beat No. 6 Oklahoma 24-19 on Saturday night to avenge a wrenching loss from last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kansas St. upsets Sooners

events.name: Missouri Tigers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw completed 20 straight passes and threw for two touchdowns, Marcus Lattimore ran for two scores and No. 7 South Carolina manhandled Missouri 31-10 and the Tigers' first Southeastern Conference road game Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shaw (20-of-21) leads No. 7 South Carolina

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw three touchdown passes to Tavon Austin and No. 8 West Virginia outlasted Maryland 31-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith, Austin team as W. Va. slips Maryland

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Manti Te'o had two interceptions as No. 11 Notre Dame picked off five Michigan passes and backup quarterback Tommy Rees sparked the Fighting Irish offense in a 13-6 win over the 18th-ranked Wolverines Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notre Dame D stifles Michigan

events.name: California Golden Bears at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Matt Barkley passed for 192 yards and threw two touchdown passes to Marqise Lee, and No. 13 Southern California bounced back from its first defeat with a 27-9 victory over California on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: USC bounces back with victory against Cal

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jeff Driskel accounted for two touchdowns, helping No. 14 Florida beat Kentucky 38-0 Saturday and extend its winning streak to 26 in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida tallies 26th straight win vs. Kentucky

events.name: UAB Blazers at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Braxton Miller ran for two touchdowns and No. 16 Ohio State overcame a lethargic, mistake-filled effort to hold off UAB 29-15 on Saturday in the Buckeyes' final tune-up before Big Ten play.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sluggish Ohio St. prevails

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Brandon Carter had a 68-yard touchdown on one of his one-handed catches, linebacker Kenny Cain recovered a fumble along with two interceptions and 17th-ranked TCU beat Virginia 27-7 Saturday for its 11th consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU beats UVa, wins FBS-best 11th straight

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Sean Mannion passed for a career-high 379 yards and two touchdowns, Oregon State put the clamps on No. 19 UCLA's offense, and the unbeaten Beavers opened their Pacific-12 Conference season by stunning the Bruins 27-20 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beavers drop No. 19 Bruins

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Florida Intl Golden Panthers

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgewater passed for two touchdowns and ran for another score in the return to his home city, and No. 20 Louisville remained unbeaten by holding off Florida International 28-21 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridgewater powers No. 20 Louisville past FIU

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Le'Veon Bell rushed for a career-high 253 yards and a touchdown to help stagnant Michigan State avoid a major upset with a 23-7 win over Eastern Michigan on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bell, Michigan State edge Eastern Michigan

events.name: South Alabama Jaguars at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: This was exactly the kind of lackluster effort that Mississippi State coach Dan Mullen hoped to avoid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sluggish Mississippi St. downs South Alabama

events.name: Idaho State Bengals at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Rex Burkhead ran for 119 yards and two touchdowns and No. 25 Nebraska made quick work of Idaho State in a 73-7 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burkhead, Nebraska easily dispatch Idaho St.

events.name: UMass Minutemen at Miami (OH) RedHawks

headlines.description: Miami (Ohio) 27, UMass 16
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami (Ohio) 27, UMass 16

events.name: Bowling Green Falcons at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Logan Thomas helped Virginia Tech find its running game and the defense showed up, too, as the Hokies bounced back from a humbling loss a week ago with a 37-0 victory against Bowling Green.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas, Va. Tech rebound, sink Bowling Green

events.name: UTEP Miners at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: James White rushed for a pair of touchdowns Saturday, helping Wisconsin overcome the early loss of Montee Ball in a 37-26 victory over UTEP.
headlines.shortLinkText: Badgers lose Ball, rout UTEP

events.name: New Hampshire Wildcats at Old Dominion Monarchs
Central Michigan Chippewas at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Central Michigan's David Harman drilled a 47-yard field goal with three seconds left, and the Chippewas scored nine points in the final 45 seconds and stunned Iowa 32-31 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: C. Michigan edges Iowa on Harman's late FG

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at Tulane Green Wave

headlines.description: Jeff Scott ran for two touchdowns and Mississippi piled up 304 yards rushing in a 39-0 victory over winless Tulane on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ole Miss rushes for 304 yards in rout of Tulane

events.name: Army Black Knights at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Michael Campanaro scored a career-best three touchdowns, and Wake Forest's defense came up with a key fourth-quarter stop to beat Army 49-37 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wake racks up 517 total yards, outlasts Army

Connecticut Huskies at Western Michigan Broncos

headlines.description: Alex Carder threw for 237 yards and a touchdown to lead Western Michigan to a 30-24 win over Connecticut on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: W. Michigan tops UConn for 2nd straight season

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Mike James scored untouched on a 25-yard run, moments after Miami stopped Georgia Tech quarterback Tevin Washington on fourth-and-inches on the first possession of overtime, giving the Hurricanes a wild 42-36 win Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami scores last 23 points, tops GT in overtime

events.name: South Dakota Coyotes at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Venric Mark ran for 117 yards and three touchdowns to lead Northwestern to an easy 38-7 victory over South Dakota on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mark's 3 TDs ease Northwestern by S. Dakota

events.name: East Carolina Pirates at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Gio Bernard scored two touchdowns in his return from a knee injury and North Carolina took over after halftime to beat East Carolina 27-6 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bernard has 2 TDs in return as UNC sinks ECU

events.name: Temple Owls at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Matt McGloin threw for a career-high 318 yards and ran for two short scores, and linebacker Michael Mauti led another strong defensive effort to lead Penn State to a 24-13 win Saturday over Temple.
headlines.shortLinkText: McGloin's career day keys Penn State

events.name: Gardner-Webb Bulldogs at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Tino Sunseri passed for 344 yards and three touchdowns to lead Pittsburgh past overmatched Gardner-Webb 55-10 on Saturday.

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Northern Illinois Huskies

headlines.description: Northern Illinois rallied from a 23-13 fourth quarter deficit to defeat Kansas 30-23 Saturday afternoon. The Huskies (3-1) victory moved its home field winning streak to 17 games, while the Jayhawks (1-3) lost their 14th straight road contest.
headlines.shortLinkText: N. Illinois' 4th-quarter rally ups home streak

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Jordan Webb scored on a 4-yard run in the final seconds, the last of three Colorado touchdowns in the final 7 minutes, to beat Washington State 35-34 on Saturday in the Pac-12 Conference opener for both teams.

headlines.description: Keith Wenning connected with Willie Snead for a 19-yard touchdown pass with 1:02 left as Ball State rallied to beat South Florida 31-27 on Saturday.

headlines.description: Playing in his first career game, North Carolina State freshman Shadrach Thornton ran for 145 yards and two touchdowns in the Wolfpack's convincing 52-14 win over The Citadel on Saturday night.
